    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="C4 PTR Game and Account Settings Overview" class="article-title">
          C4 PTR Game and Account Settings Overview
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2026-06-02T19:53:36Z" title="2026-06-02T19:53:36Z" data-datetime="relative">June 02, 2026 19:53</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/52250841633811-C4-PTR-Game-and-Account-Settings-Overview/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>The C4 PTR settings menu gives you access to account options, character options, support tools, keypair import/export, and basic game settings.</p><p>This article gives a quick overview of the options available from the settings menu.</p><blockquote><p><strong>Note:</strong> C4 PTR is still in development, so some settings and menu options may change over time.</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4W9S6973CXZEQECJ45JEDX">Where to find the settings menu</h2><p>The settings menu is available from the player menu in the top-right corner of the screen.</p><p>From there, you can access several account and game options.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 821/111;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52250841622291" width="821" height="111"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WA0SGD5TCJ25J2T7GJBMH">Account Settings</h2><p>The <strong>Account Settings</strong> area shows account-related information, including:</p><ul><li data-list-item-id="ebf3691e483f38895da8717f418a9b65b">Wallet balances</li><li data-list-item-id="eca6c7aa38acaf4c0ff4d2985aeed15f1">Daily check-in streak</li></ul><p>You can check in once per 24 hours.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 777/753;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52250841623443" width="777" height="753"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WA5D2CZRQ9SF594YNQGXT">View Character Info</h2><p>The <strong>View Character Info</strong> option allows you to access character-related account actions.</p><p>From this area, you can deposit or withdraw:</p><ul><li data-list-item-id="e7a04f30670a260a45b6e7e62e868bb58">ATLAS</li><li data-list-item-id="e3aa9393c22206cfab2f1ad3bf53ecb1a">SOL</li><li data-list-item-id="e5b294d5b6ab0544349d5d01ac0bb4362">ZINK</li></ul><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 1139/1274;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52250847694611" width="1139" height="1274"></figure><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WA92PN6M9E45PP8134MG6">Change Character</h2><p>The <strong>Change Character</strong> option allows you to switch characters or create alternate characters.</p><p>This works similarly to character selection in other MMO-style games, where you can create and play more than one account or character.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 1316/544;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52250847696147" width="1316" height="544"></figure><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WAEKN7G29CW4MSD8547ZQ">Help &amp; Support</h2><p>The <strong>Help &amp; Support</strong> option gives you another way to access support resources.</p><p>From there, you can reach reporting tools, forms, and support information.</p><p>Use this option if you need to report a bug, submit feedback, request a feature, or create a support ticket.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 1369/646;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52250841625619" width="1369" height="646"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WAK7D30H70D3KQEGTPWRC">Disconnect Wallet</h2><p>The <strong>Disconnect Wallet</strong> option signs your wallet out of the game.</p><blockquote><p><strong>Important for PTR:</strong> If you disconnect your wallet during PTR, you may need your keypair to get back into your saved game.</p></blockquote><p>Make sure you understand the import/export keypair options before disconnecting.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WART6A44VZWRWSRTHA2QV">Import Keypair</h2><p>The <strong>Import Keypair</strong> option allows you to restore a saved PTR game using a keypair file.</p><p>Use this if you previously exported your keypair and need to access the same PTR profile again.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WAYQDSJDYQG02QAA9APXK">Export Keypair</h2><p>The <strong>Export Keypair</strong> option allows you to save your PTR game as a keypair file.</p><p>You can use this file later to import your saved PTR profile again or access it from another device.</p><p>Because C4 PTR uses test assets and test wallet information, keeping your exported keypair safe is important if you want to keep access to the same PTR profile.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WB5FXTGE2QWB3K0SRKPTG">Command Settings</h2><p>The <strong>Command Settings</strong> option controls basic game settings.</p><p>This includes basic audio and visual settings for the game.</p><p><img src="/hc/article_attachments/52250847704979" width="554" height="550"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4WB99W8KJTZ1RZR5S8CNFM">Summary</h2><p>The C4 PTR settings menu lets you manage important account and game options, including character information, support access, wallet disconnection, keypair import/export, and command settings.</p><p>Before disconnecting your wallet or switching devices, make sure you have exported your keypair if you want to keep access to the same PTR profile.</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer>
        <div class="article-footer">
          
